==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Photosculpture
<hw>Pho`to*sculp"ture</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Photo-</ets> + <ets>sculpture</ets>.]</ety> <def>A process in
which, by means of a number of photographs simultaneously taken from
different points of view on the same level, rough models of the figure
or bust of a person or animal may be made with great
expedition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Photosphere</ent>⟦br⟧
